      <p>So on the one hand we have the mantra in the pharmaceutical industry of &#8220;fail early, fail often,&#8221; which is fine for manaagement, but for the people doing the work they can hear the underlying message of &#8220;Cut, cut, cut.&#8221; They will do what any rational person would do &#8211; fake the results and pass the buck. Heck they&#8217;ll probably even get a recognition as a &#8220;rising young star,&#8221; and take the job of someone who had more integrity and got sacked.</p>

